A Minna High Court has sentenced a Rapist, Ugochukwu Unadumene to life imprisonment for raping a female Youth Corper in Agaie local government area of Niger state. Ugochukwu had raped the victim who is serving in Lapai when the victim boarded his motorcycle along the Lapai-Agaie road in May 2018. The suspect was said to have diverted into a forest along the road and raped the suspect. The suspect was apprehended and investigated by Agaie division after the victim lodged a complaint against him. The Niger state Police Command had filed two charges before the High Court in Minna for prosecution. The Police had eight witnesses in proof of the allegation while the accused person who entered into his defence, denied the allegation. Despite his denial, the Presiding Judge of the High Court 3 Minna, Justice Abdullahi Mika’ilu after listening to all parties involved, sentenced the suspect to life imprisonment without option of fine for the offence of rape and one year imprisonment without option of fine for the offence of voluntary causing hurt without provocation, both sentenced are to run concurrently. The Suspect’s application for allocutus was taken and refused. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Wasiu Abiodun in a statement expressed the excitement of the Command for successfully convicting a rape suspect. He reiterated that the Police and other security agencies in the state will not rest on its oars in tackling crime and criminality in the environment in its bid towards securing and safeguarding Niger State.